Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.98,0:12:32.99,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\an4\fnCardo\c&HF8F8F8&\fs42\blur0.625\pos(172.5,675)\b1}Three-dimensionsal Maneuver Device Training{\fnMS PMincho\b1\fs30}②{\fnCardo\fs42\b1}\NGreat physical and leg strength, coupled with spatial\Nrecognition abilities, as well as the mental strength\Nto not waver in the midst of panic, are crucial qualities.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:34.86,0:12:36.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Follow the basics and you should be fine.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:37.57,0:12:40.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't think about doing it well or anything.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:40.12,0:12:42.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pay attention to your front and rear balance,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:42.62,0:12:46.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and gently rest your weight upon the belts \Non your waist and the back of your legs.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:46.29,0:12:48.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take it slow and you'll be okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:48.46,0:12:50.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even I could do it, after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:50.21,0:12:53.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, I think I can do it this time.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:53.17,0:12:54.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Raise me up, Armin.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:54.93,0:12:55.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:10.02,0:13:11.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Dazz.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:11.48,0:13:15.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that the guy who said he'd \Nslaughter all the Titans yesterday?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:16.49,0:13:19.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, he'll probably be on \Nreclaimed land by tomorrow.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:19.58,0:13:22.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no food for the useless, after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:22.16,0:13:22.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eren.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:24.58,0:13:26.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't pay them any mind.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:26.83,0:13:29.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You still have tomorrow to get the hang of it.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:29.67,0:13:31.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How pathetic.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:31.71,0:13:35.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At this rate, exterminating them is...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:35.22,0:13:37.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't aim for that anymore.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:38.34,0:13:40.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:40.05,0:13:42.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I said you shouldn't aim to be a soldier.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:43.14,0:13:47.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, throwing away your \Nlife isn't the way to fight.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:47.14,0:13:48.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look here.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:48.52,0:13:51.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On that day, I witnessed \Neverything that happened.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:51.44,0:13:54.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you think I'm gonna give up \Nbecause of something like this?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:54.40,0:13:57.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But your resolution has nothing to do with it.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:57.57,0:13:59.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? Why?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:59.95,0:14:02.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the one that decides whether \Nor not you can become a soldier...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:02.62,0:14:03.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,isn't you.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:11.13,0:14:16.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not like I'm telling you to return \Nto reclaimed land by yourself.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:12.29,0:14:13.46,Dialogue_Alt,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Let's go, Armin.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:13.80,0:14:15.67,Dialogue_Alt,,0,0,0,,{\an8}O-Okay...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:16.09,0:14:17.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:18.22,0:14:21.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, I'll go with you.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:26.43,0:14:29.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Um, so...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:29.85,0:14:32.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying I can have that?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:50.96,0:14:53.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A trick to posture control?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:53.63,0:14:57.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but since I'm a genius, \Nall I can say is "feel it".
Dialogue: 10,0:14:57.67,0:15:00.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, I'd like {\i1\b1}you{\i0\b0} to teach {\i1\b1}me{\i0\b0} something.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:00.01,0:15:04.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The secret to keeping your sanity after \Ncompletely embarrassing yourself, that is.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:04.81,0:15:08.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You guys, I just begged you for your help.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:08.81,0:15:13.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But yesterday, didn't you say\N"The powerless should just leave"?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:14.77,0:15:16.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, maybe I'm mistaken.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:16.28,0:15:19.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or was it "The talentless have \Nno choice but to leave"?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:19.49,0:15:20.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which was it again?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:21.70,0:15:22.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:22.74,0:15:27.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard you two were naturals, Bertolt, Reiner!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:27.95,0:15:32.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but I can't think of a trick to hanging.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:32.00,0:15:34.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think I can give you any helpful tips.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:35.38,0:15:36.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:36.46,0:15:38.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess all we can do is hope\N for the best tomorrow.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:40.30,0:15:44.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You two are from Shiganshina District, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:44.43,0:15:45.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we are.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:45.76,0:15:49.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you must be familiar with \Nhow terrifying the Titans are.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:49.18,0:15:51.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So why are you trying to become soldiers?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:54.06,0:15:59.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unlike Eren, I wasn't personally \Nstricken by the threat of the Titans.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:00.11,0:16:06.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just that whenever I thought of the monarchy \Nthat implemented such a reckless recapture plan,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:06.03,0:16:08.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I felt like I couldn't sit still and do nothing.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:08.29,0:16:09.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:09.87,0:16:11.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are you two from?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:12.54,0:16:17.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Reiner and I are from a village deep in \Nthe mountains, southeast of Wall Maria.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:18.34,0:16:19.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:19.51,0:16:20.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:20.92,0:16:25.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unlike the flourishing villages along the \Nriver, news didn't get to us very quickly.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:25.93,0:16:29.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Titans came before we \Nheard anything, after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:30.77,0:16:32.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was in the dawn.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:33.23,0:16:35.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cattle were strangely excited
Dialogue: 10,0:16:35.85,0:16:39.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and I heard unfamiliar tremors \Ngradually growing louder.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:40.03,0:16:44.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eventually, I realized they were \Nthe footsteps of something.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:44.86,0:16:48.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, when I hurriedly opened the window...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:56.67,0:16:59.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't... um...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:59.59,0:17:01.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,remember much after that.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:01.92,0:17:03.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone was in a dire state of disorder.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:03.76,0:17:07.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, why are you suddenly bringing that up?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:07.43,0:17:08.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:08.89,0:17:11.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Basically, what I'm trying to say is...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:11.93,0:17:15.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You guys are probably different from them.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:16.02,0:17:17.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Them?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:17.02,0:17:20.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The people here who know nothing \Nabout the fear the Titans bring.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:20.65,0:17:21.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:28.24,0:17:34.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The main reason they're here is to \Nabide by the expectations of society.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:34.00,0:17:38.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Swayed by public opinion that people who become \Nproducers after turning twelve are cowards,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:38.00,0:17:41.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,they enlisted in the Training Corps.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:42.17,0:17:45.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Despite what I say, I'm no different from them.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:46.63,0:17:49.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I became a soldier aiming to work \Nfor the Military Police Brigade
Dialogue: 10,0:17:49.64,0:17:51.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,within the inner walls where it's safe.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:51.47,0:17:55.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that doesn't seem possible, \NI might abandon training.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:55.81,0:17:58.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't have a will of my own.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:59.73,0:18:04.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Valuing your life is nothing to be ashamed of.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:07.11,0:18:07.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:08.82,0:18:11.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,going to return to my lost homeland.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:11.45,0:18:14.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the only drive I have.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:15.12,0:18:18.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going back, no matter what.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:20.00,0:18:21.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:22.46,0:18:24.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What might your goals be?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:26.72,0:18:27.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:32.97,0:18:35.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,thought to myself that I have to kill them.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:36.22,0:18:39.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That I have to slaughter them \Nall with my own two hands.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:40.27,0:18:42.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what I thought.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:47.11,0:18:51.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying that, even after encountering \Nthe Titans, you weren't overcome by fear?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:51.70,0:18:52.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:52.74,0:18:57.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, at this point, it's uncertain whether \Nor not I can even become a soldier.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:17.14,0:19:19.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Check your equipment and readjust your belts.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:19.64,0:19:21.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll do fine tomorrow.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:22.56,0:19:24.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you can do it.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:24.86,0:19:27.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eren Jaeger, was it?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:27.82,0:19:30.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, thanks.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:30.49,0:19:32.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Reiner Braun, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:42.83,0:19:45.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eren Jaeger, are you prepared?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:45.88,0:19:47.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sir!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:47.09,0:19:48.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1\b1}I'll do it.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:48.42,0:19:49.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1\b1}I'll do it!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:50.47,0:19:55.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1\b1}I may not have the aptitude, \Nbut my guts are second to none.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:56.97,0:19:58.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Begin!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:05.98,0:20:07.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1\b1}Forget reason.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:07.82,0:20:09.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1\b1}I don't even have a basis.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:09.78,0:20:12.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1\b1}But this is all I've got!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:13.49,0:20:14.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1\b1}This is...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:14.95,0:20:16.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1\b1}my weapon!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:21.20,0:20:22.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1\b1}I did it.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:22.71,0:20:24.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1\b1}I can do it!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:33.43,0:20:37.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I... I can still...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:39.56,0:20:40.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let him down.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:45.40,0:20:48.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:49.23,0:20:52.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wagner, switch belts with Jaeger.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:52.40,0:20:53.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Sir!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:01.75,0:21:04.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You had defective equipment.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:04.37,0:21:08.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The metal fixtures on your belt were damaged.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:08.59,0:21:11.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though this is the first I've \Nheard of faulty fixtures...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:11.92,0:21:14.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems there's a need to start \Nchecking them during maintenance.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:14.97,0:21:18.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then that means he... managed to stay \Nupright with faulty equipment for a bit...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:18.89,0:21:20.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:20.43,0:21:23.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Th-Then what about my aptitude evaluation?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:24.35,0:21:25.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see no issues.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:25.85,0:21:27.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Devote yourself to training.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:28.40,0:21:29.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1\b1}I did it!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:29.36,0:21:30.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1\b1}I pulled it off!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:31.19,0:21:32.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1\b1}How's that, Mikasa?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:32.61,0:21:33.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1\b1}I can do it!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:34.44,0:21:36.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1\b1}I can fight the Titans!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:36.91,0:21:40.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1\b1}There's no need for me to depend on you anymore!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:41.49,0:21:43.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like it worked out somehow.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:43.66,0:21:46.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His eyes are saying, "How's that?".
Dialogue: 10,0:21:46.00,0:21:46.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:49.00,0:21:53.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's relieved that he won't \Nhave to be separated from me.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:57.09,0:22:03.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1\b1}Grisha, today, your son has become a soldier.
Dialogue: 1,0:22:39.62,0:22:44.58,ED_Eng,,0,0,0,,{\be3\fad(250,250)}Your dream is where my heart belongs.
Dialogue: 1,0:22:39.62,0:22:44.58,ED_Rom,,0,0,0,,{\be3\fad(250,250)\k10}{\k15}so{\k18}no {\k43}yu{\k17}me {\k34}wa {\k18}ko{\k36}ko{\k32}ro {\k18}no {\k40}i{\k12}ba{\k192}sho{\k10}
